@HS2ltd What an extraordinary tweet when right now in Jones Hill Wood you are using light pollution and noise to disturb the Barbastelle bat colony. Its existence has stopped you felling more ancient woodland because you failed to obtain the correct bat licence! #hs2

@GeorgeMonbiot
@Feargal_Sharkey @jonhgurr @TimesRadio @alexisconran @DefraGovUK @Ofwat @EnvAgency @thameswater @WandleForum How and who can we petition to get this sorted out?

We are working to create a suite of wetland #habitats at the former Rugeley Power Station. This will help increase capacity to hold water in high flood events reducing damage downstream. The new habitats will be beneficial to a range of wetland species. #LetNatureHelp @EnvAgency https://t.co/z9IWi1tAB8

@jamespearson88 @EnvAgencyMids @DaveThroupEA See it often this time of year in North Yorkshire. Don't know what the answer is but soil is a finite resource and should be retained, if we keep in like this it will run out one day.

Our teams are out in Yorkshire checking temporary flood defences ahead of heavy rainfall tomorrow (images show Batley and Copley). Keep an eye on your local flood risk and be prepared to take action if you are at risk https://t.co/OVBXgMyngb #PrepareActSurvive #floodaware https://t.co/yP2gPSpvWj
